             sworn.</p>
               <p>I live opposite the warehouse; I saw the prisoner come out with a basket, and brushes in it.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>The brushes were my own; I made brushes, and sold them to Mr. Mayer for above a twelvemonth.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner called a witness, who deposed, that he was of opinion, that there was nothing so particular in the work that a man could swear to. He called another witness, who gave him a good character.)</p>
               <p>
